		<title class="- topic/title "><ph props="autonumber">252.232-7012</ph>  PERFORMANCE-BASED PAYMENTS–WHOLE-CONTRACT BASIS.</title>
		<conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody ">
			<p class="- topic/p ">As prescribed in <ph outputclass="Hyperlink" class="- topic/ph ">232.1005-70</ph>(a), use the following clause:</p>
			<p class="- topic/p ">PERFORMANCE-BASED PAYMENTS-WHOLE-CONTRACT BASIS (MAR 2014)</p>
			<p outputclass="List1" class="- topic/p ">(a)  Performance-based payments shall form the basis for the contract financing payments provided under this contract, and shall apply to the whole contract.  The performance-based payments schedule (Contract Attachment ____) describes the basis for payment, to include identification of the individual payment events, evidence of completion, and amount of payment due upon completion of each event.</p>
			<p outputclass="List1" class="- topic/p ">(b)(i)  At no time shall cumulative performance-based payments exceed cumulative contract cost incurred under this contract.  To ensure compliance with this requirement, the Contractor shall, in addition to providing the information required by FAR 52.232-32, submit supporting information for all payment requests using the following format:</p>
